  <section class="section" id="features">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <div class="eyebrow">Why Inkwell</div>
        <h2 style="max-width: 22ch;">Software for writing, by people who would rather be <em>reading</em>.</h2>
        <p class="lede">Most blogging platforms are built for marketing teams. Inkwell is built for writers — and for the developers who'd like writers to have something good.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-grid">
        <article class="feature reveal" data-delay="1">
          <span class="no">I.</span>
          <h3>Writing comes <em>first</em></h3>
          <p>A composer with no chrome — title, italic lede, serif body. Inkwell saves as you write, so the only thing on the page is the words. Markdown, slash-commands, and a real focus mode that hides everything else.</p>
          <div class="meta-row">The Editorial Desk · the admin you'll actually like</div>
        </article>
        <article class="feature reveal" data-delay="2">
          <span class="no">II.</span>
          <h3>Yours to <em>host</em></h3>
          <p>A .NET 10 application you run on your own server. No vendor, no metered usage, no algorithm. Multi-tenant by design — an agency can run a hundred client blogs from a single deploy with isolated domains.</p>
          <div class="meta-row">SQL Server · PostgreSQL · SQLite · Docker</div>
        </article>
        <article class="feature reveal" data-delay="3">
          <span class="no">III.</span>
          <h3>Twenty Layouts, <em>fifteen</em> Presets</h3>
          <p>Eleven modern Layouts and nine editorial ones — each with fifteen colour Presets. Three hundred ready-made combinations. Switch any time, or commission a Layout of your own from the Press.</p>
          <div class="meta-row">CSS variable swap · sub-second preset change</div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

